{"lemma":"لِصٌّ","slug":"لِصٌّ","root":"ل.ص.ص","root_slug":"ل-ص-ص","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ص-ص","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37730"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%90%D8%B5%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thief, robber","examples":[{"text":"مَكَانَكَ أَيُّهَا ٱللِّصُّ!","english":"Stop there, thief!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thief","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to steal","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to do secretly","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to close (the door)","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be a thief, to be thievish, to steal repeatedly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have teeth close together"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have hunched shoulders, to stoop (of a person or horse)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have one's thighs close together (of a woman)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be narrow (of one's forehead)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have unevenly oriented horns (of a sheep)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَصَّ (laṣṣa, “to steal, to do secretly, to close (the door)”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete","transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Ancient Greek λῃστής (lēistḗs)."},"ipa":["/lisˤsˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37730","headword_ar":"لِصٌّ","root":"lS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luS~N","text_ar":"لُصٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the latter mentioned by As, (Msb,) but only the former known to Sb, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~N","text_ar":"لَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thief; a robber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Msb, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laSotN","text_ar":"لَصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"substituted for the [second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the form of the word changed because of the substitution, or it is a dial. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~N","text_ar":"لِصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is said by Lh to be of the dial. of Teiyi and of some of the Ansár, and also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSotN","text_ar":"لِصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luSotN","text_ar":"لُصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lSt","text_ar":"لصت"},{"kind":"text","text":":) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~apN","text_ar":"لِصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~apN","text_ar":"لَصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~N","text_ar":"لِصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luS~N","text_ar":"لُصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~N","text_ar":"لَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luSuwSN","text_ar":"لُصُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, S, M, Msb, K,) and of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSaSapN","text_ar":"لِصَصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, TA,) and of the first (M, TA) and second, (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSaASN","text_ar":"لِصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloSaASN","text_ar":"اَلْصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2660},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [and in the TA said to be so in the T: but this is probably a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSaASN","text_ar":"لِصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": for ISd says,] the word has no pl. of pauc.: (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaS~apN","text_ar":"مَلَصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-pl. n.: (IJ, M:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~apN","text_ar":"لِصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~apN","text_ar":"لَصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~aAtN","text_ar":"لِصَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~aAtN","text_ar":"لَصَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laSaAy^iSu","text_ar":"لَصَايِصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which last is extr. [with respect to rule]: (M:) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSotN","text_ar":"لِصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luSuwtN","text_ar":"لُصُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","IDrd","TA","IJ"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%84%D8%B5/","headword_ar":"لص","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53597#1b89e0","body_html":"لص: لَصّ: قاتل مستأجر، سفاتك (بوشر)."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53597#f2e16a","body_html":"<div>لص</div><div>اللِّص: مَعْروف. ومَصْدَرُه اللصُوْصِيةُ واللصُوْصِيةُ واللصَصُ واللصَاصَةُ. وُيقَال: لَصق يَلِصق. وامْرأةٌ لِصةٌ من نِسَاء لَصائصَ وَلصّاتٍ.</div><div>والتلْصِيْصُ في البُنْيَانِ: كالتَّرْصِيْص. واللصَصُ: الْتِزَاقُ الأسْنَانِ بَعْضِها إلى بَعْضٍ. والألَص: الْمُجْتَمِعُ المَنْكِبَيْنِ يَكَادانِ يَمَسانِ أُذُنَيْه، وامْرَأَةٌ لَصّاءُ. وهو في مِرْفَقَيِ الفَرَسِ: أنْ يَنْضَما إلى زَوْرِه.</div><div>والجَبْهَةُ اللصاءُ: الضيِّقَةُ.</div><div>والرجُل اللصُوْصُ: الضيقُ. والْتَصَّ الشيْءُ: الْتَصَقَ. ولَصْلَصْتُ الوَتِدَ: إذا حَرَّكْتَه لِتَنْتَزِعَه.</div>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53597#c55d8b","body_html":"<h3>لص</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> لَصَّ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـِ He thieved, or stole: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>:) [see لُصُوصِيَّةٌ, and the other nouns mentioned therewith, some of which, if not all, are <abbr title=\"apparently\">app.</abbr> <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. ns</abbr>. of this verb:] and ↓ تلصّص signifies the same; or he was thievish: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) [or he practised theft:] or he thieved, or stole, repeatedly: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) and he acted as a spy; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> تَجَسَّسَ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> لَصَّ الشَّىْءَ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَصٌّ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) [in the <abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr> لِصٌّ,] He stole the thing: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) [and] he did the thing secretly, or covertly. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> لَصَّ بَابَهُ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَصٌّ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) He closed, or locked, his door; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> أَغْلَقَهُ and أَطْبَقَهُ; (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) as also رَصَّهُ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> لَصَّ, [<abbr title=\"apparently\">app.</abbr> in the sec. <abbr title=\"Persian (Farsi)\">Pers\\.</abbr> لَصِصْتَ, and <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـَ and <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَصَصٌ,] His teeth (أَضْرَاس) were near together, so that no interstice was seen between them. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) [This verb probably has all the significations indicated by the explanations of لَصَصٌ below.]<span class=\"sense\">2</span> لصّص بُنْيَانَهُ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> تَلْصِيصٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) He made his building firm and compact; or firm and strong; <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> رَصَّصَهُ; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) of which it is a <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> form. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) 5 تَلَصَّّ see 1.<span class=\"sense\">8</span> إِلْتَصَ3َ التصّ It stuck, or adhered, (<abbr title=\"al-Saghānī, author of the ʿUbāb and the Takmilah fī al-Ṣiḥāḥ\">Sgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) بِهِ to him. (<abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>.) لِصٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ لُصٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) the latter mentioned by <abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) but only the former known to <abbr title=\"Sibawayh\">Sb</abbr>, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) and لَصٌّ, (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) A thief; a robber; (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) as also لَصْتٌ, with ت substituted for the [second] ص, and the form of the word changed because of the substitution, or it is a <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> form of لِصٌّ, and is said by <abbr title=\"El-Lihyanee (Abu al-Ḥasan al-Liḥyānī)\">Lh</abbr> to be of the <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> of Teiyi and of some of the Ansár, and also pronounced لِصْتٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) and لُصْتٌ: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, art. لصت:) <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr> لِصَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) or لَصَّةٌ: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of لِصٌّ and لُصٌّ (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and لَصٌّ, (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) لُصُوصٌ, (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and of the first, لِصَصَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and of the first (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) and second, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) لِصَاصٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) or أَلْصَاصٌ: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) [and in the <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr> said to be so in the <abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>: but this is probably a mistake for لِصَاصٌ: for <abbr title=\"Ibn Sīdah\">ISd</abbr> says,] the word has no <abbr title=\"plural of paucity, جَمْعُ فِلَّةٍ\">pl. of pauc.</abbr>: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) and مَلَصَّةٌ is a <abbr title=\"quasi-plural noun, إِسْمُ جَمْعٍ\">quasi-<abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> n.</abbr>: (<abbr title=\"Ibn Jinnī\">IJ</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) the <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of لِصَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) or لَصَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) is لِصَّاتٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) and لَصَّاتٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and لَصَائِصُ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) which last is <abbr title=\"extraordinary (with respect to analogy or rule, with respect to usage), نَادِرٌ.\">extr.</abbr> [with respect to rule]: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) and the <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of لِصْتٌ is لُصُوتٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>.) لَصٌّ and لُصٌّ: see لِصٌّ.<br><br>لَصَصٌ Nearness together of the أَضْرَاس [or teeth, or molar teeth, or all the teeth except the central incisors,] (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) so that no interstice is seen between them; (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>;) as also رَصَصٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, art. رص.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> And Nearness together of two legs of a quadruped, and of the two thighs: and nearness together of the upper parts of the two knees: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) or nearness together of the two shoulder-joints, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or of the upper parts thereof, so that they nearly touch the ears: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) or nearness together of the two shoulder-blades: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) and a contraction of the elbows of the horse towards his [breast, or that part of it which is called the] زَوْر; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) and their cleaving to that part; which is a quality approved in a horse. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> Also, Nearness of the forehead to the eyebrow. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Qaṭṭāʿ al-Ṣiqillī\">IKtt</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> See also لُصُوصِيَّةٌ.<br><br>لَصَاصٌ: see what next follows.<br><br>لُصُوصٌ: see what next follows.<br><br>لُصُوصَةٌ: see what next follows.<br><br>لُصُوصِيَّةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr> [in the <abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr> without tesh-deed]) and لَصُوصِيَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, and in a copy of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) the latter of which is the more chaste, though the other is the regular form, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and ↓ لُصُوصَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, and so in the <abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr> in the place of the form next preceding,) or ↓ لَصُوصَةٌ, (as in some copies of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr> and in the <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) or ↓ لُصُوصٌ and ↓ لَصُوصٌ, (as in a copy of the <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) and ↓ لَصَاصٌ and ↓ لَصَصٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) Thieving; or thievishness. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) أَلَصُّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or أَلَصُّ الأَضْرَاسِ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) A man (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, A) whose [teeth called] اضراس are near together (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) so that no interstice is seen between them: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) as also أَرَصُّ: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, art. رص:) <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr> لَصَّآءُ. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> Also, the <abbr title=\"masculine, مُذَكَّرٌ\">masc</abbr>. (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) and <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr>, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or أَلَصُّ الفَخِذَيْنِ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) One whose thighs cleave together, there being no space between them. (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) [See also أَرَصُّ.] Hence, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) the Zenjee is said to be أَلَصُّ الأَلْيَتَيْنِ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) i. e. Having the buttocks cleaving together. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) And أَلَصُّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) or أَلَصُّ المَنْكِبَيْنِ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) Having the two shoulderjoints near together, almost touching the ears. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, A.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> Also the <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr>, applied to a woman, Impervia coëunti; (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>;) as also رَصَّآءُ. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, art. رص.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> And, applied to a forehead (جَبْهَة), Narrow. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> And, applied to a sheep or goat, Having one of her horns extending forwards and the other backwards. (<abbr title=\"al-Zamakhsharī\">Z</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Saghānī, author of the ʿUbāb and the Takmilah fī al-Ṣiḥāḥ\">Sgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) مَلَصَّةٌ <abbr title=\"quasi-plural noun, إِسْمُ جَمْعٍ\">quasi-<abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> n.</abbr> of لِصٌّ. (<abbr title=\"Ibn Jinnī\">IJ</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> أَرْضٌ مَلَصَّةٌ A land in which are thieves, or robbers: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) or in which are many thieves or robbers. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) غَلَقٌ مَلْصُوصٌ [A closed lock]. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.)"}]}}